<p>North Scottsdale neighborhoods like DC Ranch and Desert Ridge feature newer construction with optimal south-facing roof orientations and modern electrical systems ideal for solar installations. These areas commonly have 2,500-3,000 sq ft homes that perform well with 8-10kW solar systems. Central Scottsdale areas including Arcadia and the Biltmore corridor present opportunities for solar retrofits on mid-century homes, though some properties may require electrical upgrades. The Gainey Ranch area's luxury homes often feature tile roofs that require specialized solar mounting systems but provide excellent long-term solar platform stability.</p>

